Yeah, I guess it's not the best name. I was thinking that if there was an `IsAlgebraic.def`, it would say basically this but without the `coeff` part. I've renamed to `exists_nonzero_coeff_aeval` which hopefully communicates the content better.

```suggestion
theorem IsAlgebraic.exists_nonzero_coeff_and_aeval_eq_zero
```
It seems better to me, but I am not 100% sure.
